			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This has been a sticking point to me as long as have played the magician class and with the upcoming LDoN expansion and the ridiculous addition of an upgrade to our pbae spell when AE groups have been all but destroyed by the previous expansion and wizards getting a Cold dd upgrade comparable to Agnarr's/Sol am still baffled as to WHY magicains do not get cold based dd's.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="Rolling Eyes" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Explain to me please why we should not get one, not anymore powerful than our fire or magic dd's mind you but why not ?  We are included on every int caster focus with Cold DD foci (Fury/Wrath of Eci) we are supposed to be quasi-wizards who gave up some of our power in lieu of the power of our pets, we are the masters of elements but yet is one element we are completely impotent to control. 
<br />

<br />
A cold-based dd wouldn't make us supplant wizards as the *masters of damage* in anyway shape or form, all it would do is give us another option in situations where magic and fire are not as effective. Wizards would still have better damage spells, faster casting, better aggro mitigation therefore allowing them to nuke more freely and maintain their position as the true masters of spell based damage.
<br />

<br />
I understand why we don't get root.......I completely understand why we don't get snare.......but for the life of me can NOT understand or come up with a logical reasoning as to why we don't get a cold based nuke comparable to our fire and magic based dd's......Am I alone ??
<br />

<br />
Dalmathius Needs'Root
<br />
Arch Convoker of Dark Horizon
<br />
Zeb</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
