			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A smart person on this board once said that: 
<br />

<br />
Elementalists = master of the elementals, NOT the elements.
<br />

<br />
Which is an acceptable truth to me.
<br />

<br />
It is a class balance thing.
<br />

<br />
Nukes by nukers:
<br />
Wiz: fire, cold, and magic, anti-dragon EDIT anti-giant also
<br />
Enchanter: magic
<br />
Druid: Fire and anti-elemental EDIT: cold also
<br />
Mage: fire, magic, anti-elemental
<br />

<br />
(I hope it is correct)
<br />

<br />
Note that only the wizard have both elements, magic, and anti-special creature. The wizard is designed to be the ultimate nuker, the most versatile nuker, etc etc. Therefore the other nukers must have limitations that the wizard don't have. If we get cold, wizards will loose a class defining uniqueness. Besides, if we get cold, we will not get as great a pet upgrade that we would otherwise.
<br />

<br />
This discussion is as old as EQ.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: druids got cold also, wizards have anti-giant<br />_________________<br />Iblis
<br />
65 magician, Heralds of Dawn, Karana</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Iblis on Wed Aug 20, 2003 12:32 pm; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
